{
  "page": "Audience chamber (Great Pyramid)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dance_with_dragons_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti-d84tlih.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/98/Dance_with_dragons_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti-d84tlih.jpg/350px-Dance_with_dragons_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti-d84tlih.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"485\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/98/Dance_with_dragons_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti-d84tlih.jpg/525px-Dance_with_dragons_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti-d84tlih.jpg 1.5x, /images/9/98/Dance_with_dragons_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti-d84tlih.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dance_with_dragons_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti-d84tlih.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The audience chamber in the Great Pyramid, by Marc Simonetti © LeYa Brasil</div></div></div>\n<p>An <b>audience chamber</b> is located in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Great Pyramid\">Great Pyramid</a>, one level below the structure's <a href=\"/index.php/Apex_of_the_Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Apex of the Great Pyramid\">apex</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Chamber\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chamber</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Terrace\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Terrace</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chamber\">Chamber</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Chamber\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The splendorous audience chamber (or hall) is one level below the apartments at the <a href=\"/index.php/Apex_of_the_Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Apex of the Great Pyramid\">apex of the Great Pyramid</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> down a broad <a href=\"/index.php/Marble\" title=\"Marble\">marble</a> stair.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is a chilly, echoing, high-ceilinged room with tiles and walls of purple marble. Tall candles burn amongst the purple marble pillars.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The chamber has a fantastic throne  of carved and gilded wood, all in the shape of a savage <a href=\"/index.php/Harpies\" title=\"Harpies\">harpy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Terrace\">Terrace</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Terrace\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The audience chamber has its own terrace. The lower terrace and its garden are used by Daenerys and <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a> to entertain the representatives from <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> to celebrate the peace. The garden includes lemon trees and night-blooming flowers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>After her successful <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Siege of Meereen\">siege of Meereen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> takes the <a href=\"/index.php/Apex_of_the_Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Apex of the Great Pyramid\">apex of the Great Pyramid</a> for her private chambers, and uses the hall one level below as her audience chamber. Daenerys refuses to use a \"<a href=\"/index.php/Harpies\" title=\"Harpies\">harpy's</a> lap\" as a throne, so she has the old throne destroyed and its remains used for firewood. She chooses to sit a plain <a href=\"/index.php/Ebony\" title=\"Ebony\">ebony</a> bench instead, though she notes the <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereeneese</a> population considered the bench unworthy for a queen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Fishman_CaptainGroleosHead.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/Marc_Fishman_CaptainGroleosHead.jpg/250px-Marc_Fishman_CaptainGroleosHead.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"312\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/Marc_Fishman_CaptainGroleosHead.jpg/375px-Marc_Fishman_CaptainGroleosHead.jpg 1.5x, /images/3/37/Marc_Fishman_CaptainGroleosHead.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Fishman_CaptainGroleosHead.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Bloodbeard\" title=\"Bloodbeard\">Bloodbeard</a> delivers <a href=\"/index.php/Groleo\" title=\"Groleo\">Groleo</a>'s head. Art by Marc Fishman ©</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Unsullied\" title=\"Unsullied\">Unsullied</a> stand with their backs to the pillars when <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> holds court.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  Daenerys finds herself spending long hours on the bench, listening to various petitioners and official representatives. \n</p><p>When Daenerys goes missing on <a href=\"/index.php/Drogon\" title=\"Drogon\">Drogon</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Daznak%27s_Pit\" title=\"Daznak&#39;s Pit\">Daznak's Pit</a>, her consort and co-ruler, <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a>, takes over the audience chamber in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Great Pyramid\">Great Pyramid</a>. He replaces her ebony bench with two imposing thrones of gilded wood, and their tall backs are carved in the shape of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>. He chooses the right-hand throne for himself, leaving the vacant left-hand throne for[Daenerys in case she returns.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a> thinks of the new throne as the \"dragon throne\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p><p>After Hizdahr assumes control in Daenerys's absence, Barristan attends a court session in the audience chamber. Barristan sees Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gerris_Drinkwater\" title=\"Gerris Drinkwater\">Gerris Drinkwater</a>, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Archibald_Yronwood\" title=\"Archibald Yronwood\">Archibald Yronwood</a> in the rear of the hall. After <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodbeard\" title=\"Bloodbeard\">Bloodbeard</a> delivers <a href=\"/index.php/Groleo\" title=\"Groleo\">Groleo</a>'s head, Barristan unsuccessfully warns Quentyn to leave the city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser Barristan eventually deposes Hizdahr in a <i>coup d'etat</i> and is proclaimed <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Queen's Hand</a>, meaning that he is ruling in the name of the missing Daenerys. He decides to keep both the ebony bench and the dragon thrones out of the hall. He replaces them with his own new seat: a large round table in the center of the wall, surrounded by tall chairs. Barristan intends for the men seated at the table, the <a href=\"/index.php/Ruling_council_of_Meereen\" title=\"Ruling council of Meereen\">ruling council of Meereen</a>, to discuss as peers. He refuses to hold court or accept petitioners in the hall until the return of Daenerys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Her audience chamber was on the level below, an echoing high-ceilinged room with walls of purple <a href=\"/index.php/Marble\" title=\"Marble\">marble</a>. It was a chilly place for all its grandeur. There had been a throne there, a fantastic thing of carved and gilded wood in the shape of a savage <a href=\"/index.php/Harpies\" title=\"Harpies\">harpy</a>. She had taken one long look and commanded it be broken up for firewood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Audience_chamber_(Great_Pyramid)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_71\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 71\">Chapter 71</a>, Daenerys VI.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_2\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 2\">Chapter 2</a>, Daenerys I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_30\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 30\">Chapter 30</a>, Daenerys V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_50\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 50\">Chapter 50</a>, Daenerys VIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">5.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\">5.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\">5.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_59\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 59\">Chapter 59</a>, The Discarded Knight.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_70\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 70\">Chapter 70</a>, The Queen's Hand.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404010619\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.036 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.038 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1226/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9042/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 4729/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: